{"item_id": "case:vllm@0e60c925cf8c", "kind": "case", "repo": "vllm", "findings": [{"severity": "important", "category": "defensive-oversync", "claim": "The removed line `assert a2_scale == self.quant_config.a2_scale` was a device-tensor equality check placed on the MoE expert forward hot path (`AiterExperts.apply`, called from `modular_kernel.py:1205` on every MoE forward/step). Both `a2_scale` and `self.quant_config.a2_scale` are `torch.Tensor | None`; when they are tensors, `a2_scale == self.quant_config.a2_scale` produces a boolean device tensor and `assert` on it invokes `Tensor.__bool__`, forcing an implicit device→host synchronization every forward. Under CUDA/HIP graph capture on ROCm this even fails outright (hipErrorStreamCaptureUnsupported, per the commit message). Removing the assert eliminates a per-step forced sync / graph-capture break — this commit FIXES a perf/functional regression rather than introducing one.", "confidence": 0.82, "file": "vllm/model_executor/layers/fused_moe/rocm_aiter_fused_moe.py", "hot_path": true, "default_enabled": true, "leaf": "defensive-oversync", "suggested_benchmark": "microbench_templates/defensive-oversync.py"}], "leak_attempt": false, "latency_s": 22.08, "n_turns": 1, "cost": 0.3377965, "gate": false, "decomposed": false, "n_groups": 1, "scenario": "low", "tokens": {"in": 0, "out": 0}}
